12 September 2014The Minister of Communications, Ms Faith Muthambi will on Sunday, 14 September 2014 launch the Thusong Service Centre Week at Mamelodi in Pretoria.The campaign which runs from Monday, 15th to Friday, 19th September 2014 is a week of heightened communication on the achievements of the Thusong Service Programme and it forms part of Public Service Month. .Members of the media are invited to join Minister Muthambi as she does a walkabout at the Mamelodi Thusong Service Centre and interact with residents and public service beneficiaries.Media programme Visit to Mamelodi Thusong Service Centre and interaction with service beneficiaries Time: 09h15 Venue: Mamelodi Thusong Service Centre, 19864 Makhubela Street, Mamelodi West, Pretori Formal launch of the campaign and delivery of the keynote address Time: 10h00 Venue: Denlyn Mall in Mamelodi, PretoriaThusong Service Centres are one-stop-centres providing a cluster of government services in an integrated manner. Through these centres, government is able to ensure that people have access to government services and information within their communities, particularly in remote and sparsely populated areas. Thusong Service Centres have been in existence for fifteen (15) years in provinces.For more information on the Thusong Programme visit www.thusong.gov.zaKey activities planned for the week include the following: Date Activity Led-by 14/09/2014 Launch of the Inaugural Thusong Service Centre Week. Mamelodi Thusong, Gauteng Province Minister of Communications Ms Faith Muthambi 15/09/2014 Acts of kindness event How Thusong Centres have changed lives for the better Mapodile Thusong Service Centre, Steelpoort, Limpopo Province Executive Mayor Tubatse Local Municipality Deputy CEO of GCIS, Ms Nebo Legoabe RSVPs should be directed to Pheliswa Sebati on 082 413 4609 or Irene Magwai 0728225869Enquiries: Bongiwe Gambu 0827149463 Issued by GCIS